		<td><b>NESASM3 - Using Multiple ASM files?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hello,<br /><br />I am working through Nerdy Nights right now, and everything is going well.<br /><br />I am noticing my ASM code is starting to get rather long, is there a way to incorporate multiple ASM files so I can break my code out into multiple files?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tokumaru</b> [ Mon Jul 23, 2018 11:37 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: NESASM3 - Using Multiple ASM files?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You can use the INCLUDE directive to &quot;insert&quot; the contents of a file into another (e.g. <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">.include &quot;otherfile.asm&quot;</tt>). One common solution is to break up the program in several .asm files as you see fit (modules, functions, whatever), and have a main file that includes all the others to make a cohesive ROM.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


